<SLUG> BC-LA-AUTOSHOW-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW CAR DESIGNS WILL MAKE WORLD DEBUTS AT L.A. AUTO SHOW
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY GREGORY J. WILCOX  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The world's carmakers will be taking the wraps off
at least a dozen new models at the 2000 Greater Los Angeles Auto
Show, the most world previews ever at the local trade exhibit,
officials said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The January show, themed ``California Dreamin' 2000,'' will
feature the debuts of at least four concept vehicles, said Andy
Fuzesi, the show's general manager, from four different automakers:
DaimlerChrysler, Ford Motor Co., General Motors Corp. and
Volkswagen.
</P>
<P>
   The show's title reflects the fact California lifestyles and
attitudes affect the ways people around the world perceive and use
automobiles.
</P>
<P>
   ``Manufacturers recognize that California is not only a huge
marketplace, but also a trend-setter for new ideas and products.
Consequently, they regard the L.A. Auto Show as an important part
of their strategic plans,'' Fuzesi said.
</P>
<P>
   Some of the manufacturers probably will debut more than one
concept vehicle, Fuzesi said. However, they are keeping the details
sketchy for competitive reasons.
</P>
<P>
   The show will run Jan. 8-16 &UR;  &LR; at the Los Angeles Convention
Center.
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
