FROM NEW SCIENTIST MAGAZINE (N/A Brazil, Australia, New Zealand) A.
Four-Minute Warning As the missiles approach, you've just got time
to make a strong cup of coffee. Drinking coffee could protect
people from radioactivity, say scientists in India. By Rob Edwards.
500 words. B. Indecent Exposure Despite the furore over the Belgian
food scandal, this incident is just the latest in a series of
dioxin scares around the world. By Debora MacKenzie. 1,500 words.
C. Sheer Brilliance Forgers have reason to fear a butterfly that
plays astounding tricks with light. Its dazzling iridescent wings
are a counterfeiter's nightmare. By Stephanie Pain. 3,000 words.
