HUMAN INPRINT ON CLIMATE CHANGE GROWS CLEARER As evidence that the
earth's atmosphere is warming continues to accumulate, scientists
are making slow progress towards an answer to the big, frustrating
climatic question of the day : How much of the warming can be
attributed to human activity and how much to natural causes? By
William K. Stevens. New York Times Science Times. 2,000 words +
map. _____________________________________________________________
