<P>
   MCNEELY-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ A second President Bush,
already talking about cutting federal taxes, could see the economy,
and his luck, turn downward _ just like Dad's. What then?
Conservatism? Or compassion? Will he refuse to raise taxes _ even
if it means cutting necessary services? Or raise taxes, to make
sure no one is left behind? As with much about the Texas
governor-who-would-be-president, time and circumstances will tell.
(McNeely, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   GARCIA-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Last week, I gave you a glimpse
of Austin as seen through the eyes of then Sr. Patrol Officer Wayne
Vincent. This week, we're going for a ride with Dr. Ed Racht of
Emergency Medical Services. (Arnold Garcia is editorial page editor
of the Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ If the political symbol were the
swastika and the religious document came from ``Mein Kampf,'' more
Americans would see the two wrongs the U.S. House of
Representatives has committed. That the symbol in question is the
U.S. flag and the document is the Ten Commandments makes the House
no less wrong. (John Young is opinion page editor of the Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
