   TRAVEL
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-GETAWAY _ A roundup of Fourth of July events around the
Southeast, including Old Salem in N.C., the Museum of Appalachia in
Tenn., Albertville Freedom Festival in Ala. and St. Augustine, Fla.
_ and others. (Thrasher, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 40.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-ITALY _ BOLOGNA, Italy _ Beyond the gondolas and leaning
towers, the Michaelangelos and the Botticellis, there's a part of
Italy that your travel agent probably never told you about. And yet
Emilia-Romagna is where food-loving pilgrims go to find the true
holy trinity of Italy: the pork products of Parma and Bolgna, the
fine balsamic vinegars of Modena and the world's best cheese
(parmigiano-reggiano). On his fourth Italian sojourn, a writer
surveys the bounty of the region known as the belly of Italy, with
ample forays into the churches, museum, shops, plus a final jaunt
down to the Tuscan wine towns of Montepulciano, Montalcino and
others.(Brock, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).With Color Photos and
Layout
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, July 1.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-IFYOUGO _ If Your Go sidebar giving numbers to
restaurants, lodgings mentiond in the Italy story, as well as
guidebooks and sources for further information. (Brock, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, July 1.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-BILTMORE _ After three years of restoration, the
four-room Artists' Suite on the third floor of Asheville's Biltmore
Estate is opening to the public. Also new at the Biltmore: a Garden
Treasure Walk, an outdoor adventure program called Explore Biltmore
Estate and Continuing restoration of the conservatory. (Thrasher,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). with Color Photo and Layout.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, July 1.
