<P>
   HOME AND GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   GARDENING-LIFE _ Lee May's neighbor in McCaysville has a new
greenhouse for orchids. Its an impressive and inspiring structure,
but not enough to inspire Lee to take up with orchids again. (May,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   NEWGARDEN _ The launch of a new series: ``Building a Garden:''
Sam Schwartz and Lyn Goldwoski are building a garden from the
ground up _ literally. We'll track the progress of how a Decatur,
Ga. coulpe turns a clay pit into a thing of beauty. We check in
with the homeowners each season to see what worked, what failed,
lessons learned etc. Will include site plan, plant list and
``before'' photos of the garden, to be planted in June. (Flanders,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)WITH COLOR PHOTOS AND LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   WORKSHOP-TERRACE _ Tired of mowing that lawn but don't want a
high-maintenance garen? Brad Murphy might have the solution. This
spring, Murphy created a terrace in his front yard that's half
patio half grass. (Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) with
COLOR PHOTOS AND LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   MODELHOMES _ Every weekend, scores of lookers crowd model homes.
Some are serious homebuyers, but many are just looking for
decorating tips or indulging in a favorite, usually free, leisure
activity. Vicky Foster of Fayette County, making the rounds in a
Newnan subdivision, said it's a compulsion for her. She even tours
them on vacation and often gets ideas for do-it-yourself projects.
(Lee, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 23. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   HOMEDESIGN-TIPS _ A few trade secrets on home design, from where
the designers shop to how they make the homes look larger. (Lee,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 7. WITH PHOTOS. HOME-NUTS&AMP;BOLTS _
Nuts &AMP; Bolts column from James Cummings answers reader questions
about air-conditioning fans, gardening with railroad ties and baby
birds nesting in the walls of a house. (Cummings, Dayton daily
News). 23.
</P>
<P>
   GARDEN-PROFILE _ Bela Bogner is a gardener with an extraordinary
heart. He gives away the harvest of his huge vegetable garden and
shares his knowledge of plants with anyone who asks. And these
days, he's also tending the flower garden of his wife April,
hospitalized since June 1. (Dayton daily News). 24.
</P>
