<P>
   COXNET ENTERTAINMENT 0703 KING FOR `TODAY' _ ``Today,'' the
first of the morning news shows when it debuted in 1952, is
amazingly dominant in the late '90s _ it's been the No. 1 morning
show for 181 straight weeks, almost 3(apple) years, and its
ratings' lead over ``Good Morning America'' and ``CBS This
Morning'' is enormous. And yet, look out ``Today,'' 'cause it's
only getting harder from here on out. In September, ``Good Morning
America'' moves into its new studio overlooking Times Square, and
in November, CBS unwraps its new revamped show with Bryant Gumbel
as anchor and its own street-side studio on Central Park. (Kloer,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes 3-column color photo of
TV anchor Katie Couric receiving flowers from a male figure skater.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   ROCK'S PAST RETURNS _ Cheer up, all you struggling former
