life in New York amid the Son of Sam slayings. Grade: C. (Ringel,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 19
</P>
<P>
   SOUTHPARK-REVIEW _ Those foul-mouthed miscreants from South Park
say everything they can't get away with on television in their
big-screen debut _ and much, much more. Prepare to be shocked by
the sheer amount of strong profanity in ``South Park: Bigger,
Longer &AMP; Uncut'', including words you'd never imagined, as creators
Trey Parker and Matt Stone insolently wave their middle fingers at
the Motion Picture Association of America. (Larsen, Dayton Daily
News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WILDWEST-REVIEW _ Wild Wild West is a bad, bad movie. (Larsen,
Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SOUTHPARK-REVIEW _ BOOM! Hear that? That's the tasteless bar
crashing to a woefully crude new level. But what do you expect when
you give the ``South Park'' creators 90 minutes and an R-rating?
That's like letting a mischievous 5-year-old take over a day-care
center_ the results won't be pretty, but they might be comical.
(Thompson, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WILD-WILD-REVIEW _ To shoot straight about this flick, it's
simply not well written. (Schwan, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
