<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GRILLED-SPARERIBS-2ndTake-LADN </SLUG>
 
Los Angeles: 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PACIFIC RIM SHORT RIBS &UR;
</P>
<P>
   &LR; 3 pounds beef short ribs, cut into 3-inch lengths
</P>
<P>
   1 can (8 ounces) pineapple chunks in juice
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup soy sauce
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons green pepper sauce
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon sesame oil
</P>
<P>
   t tablespoon vegetable oil
</P>
<P>
   1 green onion, chopped
</P>
<P>
   1 large garlic clove
</P>
<P>
   Fresh ginger (1-inch piece), peeled
</P>
<P>
   Place each rib bone-side down and remove excess fat with a sharp
knife. Score each rib in a crisscross pattern, cutting meat halfway
to bone.
</P>
<P>
   Place pineapple with juice, sugar, soy sauce, green pepper
sauce, oils, green onion, garlic and ginger in a food processor;
blend until smooth. Place mixture and ribs in resealable plastic
food bag or large nonreactive dish. Close bag or cover dish and
refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
</P>
<P>
   Preheat grill to medium or preheat broiler.
</P>
<P>
   Remove ribs from marinade and place on a lightly greased grill
or broiler pan. Reserve marinade and heat to boiling in a saucepan;
boil 1 minute. Cook ribs about 30 minutes, turning and basting
often with marinade until ribs are well-browned on all sides. Makes
4 servings. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COUNTRY RIBS &UR;
</P>
<P>
   &LR; 4 pounds pork baby back ribs, cut into 4-rib portions
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup deli brown mustard
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup packed brown sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup chopped onion
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup red hot pepper sauce
</P>
<P>
   Honey Mustard Dip
</P>
<P>
   Place ribs into a shallow dish. Combine remaining ingredients
except Honey Mustard Dip. Pour over ribs. Cover, refrigerate 30
minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Grill ribs over medium heat 40 minutes or until no longer pink
near bone, turning and basting often with marinade. Do not baste
during last 10 minutes of cooking.
</P>
<P>
   Serve ribs with Honey Mustard Dip. Makes 4 to 6 servings
</P>
<P>
   HONEY MUSTARD DIP: Combine 1/2 cup deli brown mustard, 1/2 cup
honey and 2 tablespoons red hot pepper sauce. Mix well. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HOISIN-GLAZED BABY BACK RIBS &UR;
</P>
<P>
   &LR; GLAZE:
</P>
<P>
   1 cup hoisin sauce
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup honey
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup red wine vinegar
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons grated fresh ginger
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon minced garlic
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon sesame oil
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons curry powder
</P>
<P>
   RIBS:
</P>
<P>
   4 to 6 pounds pork baby back ribs
</P>
<P>
   Kosher salt
</P>
<P>
   Freshly ground black pepper
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon sesame seeds
</P>
<P>
   For Glaze, in a small saucepan, over medium heat, combine hoisin
sauce, honey, vinegar, ginger, garlic, sesame oil and curry powder.
Bring to a simmer, stirring occasionally and cook over low heat 2
to 3 minutes to blend flavors. Remove from heat.
</P>
<P>
   For Ribs, season ribs liberally with salt and pepper.
</P>
<P>
   Grill indirectly over medium heat, turning halfway through
cooking time. When ribs have cooked 1 hour, start basting every 15
minutes or so with hoisin glaze, until meat is very tender and has
shrunk from ends of bones, 15 to 30 minutes more. A few minutes
before ribs are finished, sprinkle with sesame seeds.
</P>
<P>
   Remove ribs from grill and cut between the bones. Serve warm.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
</P>
<P>
   From ``Weber's Art of the Grill: Recipes for Outdoor Living''
(Chronicle Books). &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SWEET LEMON SPARERIBS &UR;
</P>
<P>
   &LR; 6 pounds pork spareribs, cut into serving pieces
</P>
<P>
   Water
</P>
<P>
   1 can (6 ounces) frozen lemonade concentrate, thawed
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup barbecue sauce
</P>
<P>
   Place pork in a Dutch oven. Add enough water to cover pork. Heat
to boiling; reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer about 1 1/2 hours
or until tender.
</P>
<P>
   Remove pork to a rectangle 13x9x2-inch baking dish. Mix lemonade
concentrate and barbecue sauce. Pour over pork; turn pork to coat
with marinade. Cover and refrigerate, turning pork occasionally, at
least 4 hours but no longer than 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
   Brush grill rack with vegetable oil. Heat coals or gas grill for
direct heat.
</P>
<P>
   Remove pork from marinade. Heat reserved marinade to a boil;
boil 1 minute.
</P>
<P>
   Grill pork, meaty sides up, uncovered, 4 inches from medium-hot
heat about 30 minutes, turning and brushing frequently with heated
marinade, until glazed and heated through. Discard any remaining
marinade. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
</P>
<P>
   From ``Betty Crocker's Great Grilling Cookbook'' (Macmillian). &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DIXIE-STYLE RIBS &UR;
</P>
<P>
   &LR; 1 cup bourbon
</P>
<P>
   1 cup water
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup molasses
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup cider vinegar
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 teaspoons cayenne pepper
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   4 slabs pork back OR spareribs
</P>
<P>
   BBQ Sauce
</P>
<P>
   Combine bourbon, water, molasses, vinegar, cayenne pepper and
salt in a nonreactive dish. Marinate ribs in mixture 4 hours;
discard marinade.
</P>
<P>
   Place ribs in center of a hot cooking grate over medium coals.
Cover grill and cook until done and meat pulls away from bone,
about 1 1/2 hours. About 15 minutes before serving, baste ribs with
BBQ Sauce. Serve remaining BBQ Sauce at table.
</P>
<P>
   BBQ SAUCE: Combine 1/2 cup mustard and 1 1/2 cups of your
favorite barbecue sauce; mix well. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SPICY BEEF BACK RIBS &QL; 
1 cup ketchup &QL; 
1/2 cup water &QL; 
1 medium onion, grated &QL; 
2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice &QL; 
1 teaspoon hot pepper sauce &QL; 
1/2 to 1 teaspoon crushed red pepper pods &QL; 
5 pounds beef back ribs, cut into 3 to 4 rib sections &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Combine ketchup, water, onion, lemon juice, pepper sauce and
pepper pods in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cook
slowly, uncovered, 10 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally; keep
warm.
</P>
<P>
   Prepare grill for indirect cooking (see Note). Place beef back
ribs, meat side up, on a grid centered over a drip pan. Cover
grill. Grill ribs 45 to 60 minutes or until tender, turning
occasionally. Brush reserved sauce over ribs and continue grilling,
covered, 10 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 servings.
</P>
<P>
   NOTE: To prepare grill for indirect cooking, arrange equal
amounts of briquets on each side of grill. Place a foil drip pan in
center between coals. Coals are ready when ash-covered,
approximately 30 minutes. Make sure coals are burning equally on
both sides.
</P>
<P>
   UNCOVERED GRILLING DIRECTIONS: Place ribs, meat side down, in
center of a double-thick rectangle of heavy duty foil. Sprinkle 2
tablespoons water over rib bones.
</P>
<P>
   To form packets, bring 2 opposite sides of foil together over
top of ribs. Fold edges over 3 to 4 times, pressing crease in
tightly each time. (Allow some air space.) Flatten foil at both
ends; crease to form triangle and fold each end over several times
toward packet, pressing tightly to seal. Place packets on grid over
low to medium coals. (To check temperature, cautiously hold hand
about 4 inches above coals. Low to medium coals will force removal
of hand in 4 to 5 seconds.)
</P>
<P>
   Grill 2 hours or until tender, turning packets over every 1/2
hour. Remove ribs from packets and place on grid. Continue grilling
10 to 20 minutes, turning once. Brush sauce over ribs; continue
cooking 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   SPICY HONEY MUSTARD RIBS &QL; 
RIBS: &QL; 
2 pounds country-style spareribs (with bone) OR your favorite ribs &QL; 
SPICY HONEY MUSTARD RUB: &QL; 
1 cup honey mustard &QL; 
1/4 cup thin soy sauce &QL; 
2 tablespoons honey &QL; 
1 tablespoon chile sauce, extra spicy &QL; 
2 teaspoons ground cumin &QL; 
2 teaspoons ground cinnamon &QL; 
4 cloves garlic, finely minced
</P>
<P>
   For Ribs, remove membrane from underside of ribs. Place ribs in
a rectangular dish or pan.
</P>
<P>
   For Spicy Honey Mustard Rub (marinade), combine all rub
ingredients and stir well. Makes 1 1/2 cups rub.
</P>
<P>
   Coat ribs evenly on both sides with rub. Marinate ribs,
refrigerated, at least 15 minutes. For more flavor, marinte up to 8
hours.
</P>
<P>
   To grill ribs, if using a gas barbecue, preheat to medium (325
degrees F.). If using charcoal or wood, prepare a fire, add ribs
and grill. Occasionally during grilling, baste ribs with extra
marinade, stopping 15 minutes before removing ribs from grill.
</P>
<P>
   To serve, cut each side of ribs in half, into 3 sections or into
individual ribs. Transfer to a heated serving platter or 4 heated
dinner plates and serve at once. Makes 4 servings.
</P>
<P>
   From ``The Great Ribs Book'' by Hugh Carpenter and Teri
Sandison, Ten Speed Press. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
RIBS WITH SPICY CARIBBEAN PINEAPPLE MARINADE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   RIBS: &QL; 
2 sides spareribs OR your favorite ribs &QL; 
SPICY CARIBBEAN PINEAPPLE MARINADE: &QL; 
1/2 fresh pineapple &QL; 
1/4 cup flavorless vegetable oil &QL; 
1/4 cup packed light brown sugar &QL; 
1/4 cup thin soy sauce &QL; 
1 tablespoon curry powder &QL; 
1 teaspoon ground allspice &QL; 
1/4 cup finely minced ginger &QL; 
1/4 cup mixed green onions, green and white parts &QL; 
1/4 cup minced cilantro sprigs &QL; 
4 serrano chiles, finely minced, including seeds
</P>
<P>
   For Ribs, remove membrane from underside of ribs. Place ribs in
a rectangular dish or baking pan.
</P>
<P>
   For Spicy Caribbean Pineapple Marinade, peel and core pineapple.
In a food processor fitted with a metal blade, puree 1/2 of
pineapple. Transfer puree to a bowl and chop remaining pineapple in
food processor. Combine chopped pineapple and pineapple puree with
remaining marinade ingredients. Stir well. Makes 3 1/4 cups
marinade.
</P>
<P>
   Coat ribs on both sides evenly with 1/2 of marinade. Marinate
ribs, refrigerated, at least 15 minutes. For more flavor, marinate
up to 8 hours; discard marinade.
</P>
<P>
   Reserve remaining marinade to serve as a sauce for ribs, but
heat to a boil before using as a sauce.
</P>
<P>
   To grill ribs, if using a gas barbecue, preheat to medium (325
degrees F.). If using charcoal or wood, prepare a fire. Add ribs
and grill. Occasionally during grilling, baste ribs with extra
boiled marinade, stopping 15 minutes before removing ribs from
grill.
</P>
<P>
   To serve, cut each side of ribs in half, into 3 sections or into
individual ribs. Transfer to a heated serving platter or 4 heated
dinner plates and serve at once accompanied by reserved boiled
sauce. Makes 4 servings.
</P>
<P>
   From ``The Great Ribs Book'' by Hugh Carpenter and Teri
Sandison, Ten Speed Press. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
BABY BACK SIZZLERS &QL; 
8 pounds loin baby back ribs &QL; 
32 ounces (Robust Wishbone) Italian dressing &QL; 
2 tablespoons hot pepper flakes &QL; 
Chinese Dragon Sauce &UR; !off! &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Marinate ribs in mixture of Italian dressing, hot pepper sauce
and red pepper flakes in refrigerator at least 8 hours.
</P>
<P>
   Smoke ribs at 225 degrees F. 3 hours and cool. Cover with
Chinese Dragon Sauce and refrigerate until ready to use. Chargrill
and baste with Dragon Sauce, which has been heated to boiling.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
</P>
<P>
   CHINESE DRAGON SAUCE: In a blender, combine 2 cups frozen
tangerine juice concentrate, 2 cups teriyaki glaze, 1 cup packed
light brown sugar, 1/4 cup spicy hot brown mustard, 1/4 cup sweet
pickle relish, 1 teaspoon sesame oil and 1 teaspoon liquid smoke.
Lightly puree to mix. Simmer in a saucepan over low heat 15 minutes
before basting ribs.
</P>
<P>
   From ``Famous Dave's Backroads and Sidestreets _ Recipes
Inspired by America's Down-Home Eateries'' by Dave Anderson. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
