<P>
   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   BUSH _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush attends events in Silicon
Valley and Fresno. Returns to Austin tonight. Spot coverage.
(Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   OLY-ATLANTA-RECORDS _ ATLANTA _ Atlanta Olympics organizer Billy
Payne pledged to hand over all boxes of Atlanta Olympic records to
federal investigators but asks that the eight boxes of records that
he labels personal should not be released to the public. ACOG
co-chairman Andrew Young ripped Congress for questioning its
interest in what Young said was an outstanding effort by the
Atlantans. Also, ACOG said it will close its doors. (Turner,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25. WITH PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (a) general news and (s) sports cateories.
</P>
<P>
   VIDEOPOKER _ GONZALES, La. _ The Cajun Circus Casino was among
video poker outlets across Louisana planning ``blackout'' parties
Wednesday night after a federal judge denied appeals to keep open
video poker operations in counties that voted out the gaming in a
referendum a year ago. (Konigsmark, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   HAITI _ MIAMI _ Seeking to gain more control over how hundreds
of millions of dollars in U.S. taxpayer money is spent in Haiti,
the Senate has passed a clause as part of a foreign aid bill that
requires the Clinton administration to report to Congress every six
months on how the country is progressing in various areas. The
clause also spells out Congress' priorities in Haiti. (Emling, Cox
News Service).
</P>
