<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-01 15:16 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6128 &Cx1f; tad-z
r t &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-GETAWAY-FESTIVALS01-C     07-01 0686
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GETAWAY-FESTIVALS01-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Southern happenings
 &HT;    By Paula Crouch Thrasher
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  Dahlonega _ Dahlonega's 24th Annual Family Day July 4
Celebration, on Sunday, features the Big Country bluegrass band,
the Red Carpet Express cloggers, Colonial demonstrations and
fireworks. 706-864-3365 or www.dahlonega.org
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Pine Mountain _ Callaway Gardens' Fourth of July Sand and Surf
Spectacular at Robin Lake Beach, on Sunday, includes beach games,
swimming, performances by Florida State University's ``Flying
High'' Circus, rides aboard the miniature train, paddleboats,
miniature golf, live music and food.
</P>
<P>
   1-800-225-5292.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Savannah _ ``Breakfast With Berendt'' features John Berendt,
author of ``Midnight in the Garden of Good and Evil,'' in Forsyth
Park at 9 a.m. Tuesday for Vintage Books' launching of the
paperback version of the best seller. Entertainment by Emma Kelly
and Ben Tucker, refreshments and proclamation read by ``town
crier'' Harry Jennings, followed by a statement from Berendt. The
writer will meet people 11 a.m.-1 p.m. at the Savannah Hilton
DeSoto Atrium, where the book will be available. 912-944-0456.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  New Orleans _ The Coca-Cola Essence Music Festival, Friday
through Sunday at the Louisiana Superdome, will feature Lauryn
Hill, R. Kelly, Erykah Badu, Brian McKnight, Monica, Deborah Cox,
Dru Hill, Will Downing and Gerald Albright, the Temptations, Patti
Labelle and Maze featuring Frankie Beverly. Tickets:
1-800-488-5252. Travel packages:
</P>
<P>
   1-800-762-9523.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Smithville, Tenn. _ The Official State and National
Championship Smithville Fiddlers' Jamboree and Crafts Festival,
Friday and Saturday, includes 31 categories of old-time Appalachian
music and dance competition. Also, juried craft show with more than
200 booths. 615-597-8500.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Cordele _ The 50th Annual Watermelon Days Festival is Monday
through July 10. The event includes entertainment,
watermelon-spitting contests and food. 912-273-1668.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Berea, Ky. _ The 18th Annual Berea Craft Festival is July 9-11
at Indian Fort Theater and features 120 crafts people from 20
states, daily crafts demonstrations, regional foods and strolling
musicians and dancers on the festival grounds. 1-800-598-5263.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Franklin, N.C. _ Perry's Water Gardens in the Cowee Valley
near Franklin will present its 17th Annual Lotus Flower Festival,
Saturday through Monday. The 14 acres of gardens feature 151 ponds
and exhibit 2,500 water lily and lotus blossoms a day in red,
orange, yellow, pink, purple, white and, new this year, black.
Also, food vendors, craft displays and picnic tables under large
weeping willows. 828-524-3264.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Boone, N.C. _ The Appalachian Summer Festival, Monday through
July 31, includes nearly 30 music, dance and theater performances
at Appalachian State University. An outdoor concert with fireworks
July 17 will feature Mary Chapin Carpenter. Tickets: 1-800-841-2787
or online at appsummer.appstate.edu.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Grandfather Mountain, N.C. _ The Highland Games, July 8-11,
celebrates Scottish traditions at this annual event in MacRae
Meadows. 828-733-2013.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Asheville, N.C. _ The Craft Fair of the Southern Highlands is
July 15-18 at the Asheville Civic Center. The fair showcases works
by the 700-member Southern Highland Craft Guild and presents
demonstrations in various media as well as live mountain music and
storytelling. 828-298-7928.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Young Harris _ The 11th season of the state's official
historical drama, ``The Reach of Song,'' continues through Aug. 22
and features local musicians and cast members in a celebration of
the Appalachian spirit and a tribute to mountain poet Byron Herbert
Reece. 1-800-262-7664.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Highlands, N.C. _ The Highlands Playhouse presents the musical
``Grease'' through Sunday. Upcoming: the farce ``Cash on Delivery''
July 7-18, the musical ``Crazy for You'' July 21-Aug. 8 and the
comedy ``Take This Man'' Aug. 11-22. 828-526-2695.
</P>
<P>
   _Paula Crouch Thrasher writes for the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
