</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    IF YOU GO: The belly of Italy
 &HT;    Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, July 7.
 &HT;    By Wendell Brock
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  GETTING THERE
</P>
<P>
   There are no nonstops from Atlanta to Bologna. Air France is now
offering a $698 round-trip with a connection through Paris.
Purchase by Friday for travel through Aug. 31 (1-800-237-2747).
Other carriers: Lufthansa (1-800-645-3880), Sabena
(1-800-955-2000), British Airways (1-800-247-9297).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  LODGING
</P>
<P>
   Prices vary according to season, so it's always a good idea to
call or fax ahead. English is spoken at most of these hotels, all
of which we stayed at.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Emilia-Romagna
</P>
<P>
   Agriturismo Cavaione. 4 Via Cavaioni, Bologna.
011-39-051-589006. Fax: 051-589060.
