   BORDER-WORKERS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ All along the Southwest border, a sophisticated system
is supplying a steady flow of immigrants _ documented and
undocumented _ for U.S. industries desperate for workers in an era
of low unemployment. The system, which has evolved from the U.S.
tradition of recruiting Mexican farm laborers, involves a broad
network of people, including ``coyotes'' who smuggle in
undocumented immigrants, businesses that house and transport
workers, recruiters who comb the border and Mexico for workers, and
the companies that hire them. By MARISA TAYLOR, STEVE STEIN and
DIANE SMITH. Story has moved in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
