<P>
   UNDATED _ Spike Lee has grown enormously as a filmmaker, and in
``Summer of Sam,'' he attempts an almost touching dramatization of
a doomed humanity. The problem is that Lee hasn't evolved nearly as
much as a storyteller. The movie feels distended and poorly worked
out, and the material needs a shaping as much as any subject he has
ever filmed. By ELVIS MITCHELL. Story has moved in ``e''
entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
