   FILM-FANATIC &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ ``My Son the Fanatic'' is the oddest thing, a comedy
about misery. What's most odd about it is that it works, and works
magnificently. Hanif Kureishi, adapting his own fiction for the
screen, has written a film about the folly of good intentions and
the necessity of delusion. By ELVIS MITCHELL. Story has moved in
``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
