Galveston landed not just any cruise line but the world's largest
to offer trips year-round from its port. After almost eight years
of negotiations, the Port of Galveston lured Carnival Cruise Lines
to its new cruise pier. By JUNE NAYLOR RODRIGUEZ. Story has moved
in ``t'' travel category. &QL; 
