   BIZBOOKS-REVIEWS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ If you're looking for investment ideas, consider
picking the brains of the best in the business. Maybe you would
like to chat with John Bogle, the founder of the Vanguard Group,
the second-largest mutual fund in the world. For a different point
of view, you may want to talk to some of the information
specialists in investing. Round that out with a talk with Harry
Markowitz, Nobel Prize winner for developing the Modern Portfolio
Theory, and you would consider yourself well-educated in the
investment business. Or you would have a book. That's what Kenneth
A. Stern thought when he interviewed all of those people for his
new book ``Secrets of the Investment All-Stars'' (Amacom, 301
pages, $25). By TERESA MCUSIC. Story has moved in ``f'' financial
category. &QL; 
