foreign marching bands have apparently killed a trip to Sidney for
the 2000 Olympics for two metro Atlanta high school bands. The band
director at Walton High School said he's received an e-mail saying
the $3,600-per-student trip may be off. A story in last Friday's
Sydney Morning Herald says Olympic officials made the decision
after nationwide outcry against foreign marchers. We're talking to
folks here who were planning on going. (Stepp, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
