<P>
   LIGHTHOUSE _ Update on moving the historic lighthouse on Cape
Hatteras. The Cape Hatteras Lighthouse is moving at the speed of
slippery soap. In the black-and-white-striped beacon's unexpectedly
rapid journey inland to safety, workers are using bars of Ivory
soap to grease the steel tracks along which the lighthouse is
moving. ''The thing is moving so well with the Ivory soap as a
lubricant that it almost rolls itself,'' said Randy Knott, chief
engineer with Atlanta-based LAW Engineering and Environmental
Services Inc., the lead engineering consultant on the lighthouse
project. (Burritt, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   GAMBLING _ The South Carolina House OKs a referendum on video
poker for November. (Manuel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
