   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   HAITI _ MIAMI _ Seeking to gain more control over how hundreds
of millions of dollars in U.S. taxpayer money is spent in Haiti,
the Senate has passed a clause as part of a foreign aid bill that
requires the Clinton administration to report to Congress every six
months on how the country is progressing in various areas. The
clause also spells out Congress' priorities in Haiti. (Emling, Cox
News Service).
