</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Cox Interactive Media names new VP
 &HT;    By Staff and news reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ The Internet services company said David B. Hills has
been named vice president of sales. Hills will be responsible for
overseeing all sales operations for Cox Interactive Media's
national network of 26 Internet city sites and three specialty
sites. Hills, 43, is an 18-year veteran of Cox-owned TeleRep, Inc.,
the nation's largest television sales representation firm, where he
served as vice president/director of TeleRep Enterprises, New York
from 1987 to 1999. Cox Interactive Media is a unit of Cox
Enterprises Inc., which owns The Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
