   BOTTOM
</P>
<P>
   NY-SUV (New York) _ Despite congested streets, narrow roadways,
aging bridges and tunnels and polluted air that, in some respects,
make the New York area uniquely inhospitable to light trucks, the
region has become one of the nation's hottest markets for sport
utility vehicles. Now, state regulators are on the verge of
proposing new registration rules that could further increase the
number of heavy vehicles on area roadways. By Keith Bradsher.
