   NIRELAND-TALKS (Belfast, Northern Ireland) _ Marathon talks to
resolve the disarmament impasse that threatens the province's peace
settlement broke off early on Friday. But a spokesman for Prime
Minister Tony Blair said they would resume on Friday morning and
end with a statement on the ``way forward.'' By Warren Hoge.
